Description: Upper body sherd of East Greek, probably Aeolian, grey ware pottery closed vase, perhaps amphora; exterior: worn grey slip; numerous mica inclusions; inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Object owned and held by the Fitzwilliam Museum, Cambridge. This record is included in the British Museum database as part of the Museum’s Naukratis Project, a research collaboration that aims to virtually re-unite finds from the ancient port city of Naukratis, now distributed over 80 museums worldwide.
Bibliographic references: Gardner 1888 / Naukratis II (p. 65, no. 793, pl. XXI, no. 793)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 686, no. 444)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.005)
